      "title": "Rearrange execute details sidebar: priority/state row and active-agent/time row",
      "description": "In the execute task details sidebar, restructure the layout so that:\n1. Priority badge and state indicator appear on the same row, positioned as the first row of content below the sidebar header.\n2. In the yellow 'Active' callout, place the agent name (e.g. 'Active: Coder') and the current execution elapsed time (e.g. '4m 4s') on the same row, with the agent on the left and the timer on the right.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Priority icon/label and state badge render inline on a single row directly below the header.\n- The yellow callout displays 'Active: <Agent>' left-aligned and elapsed time right-aligned on one row.\n- Layout remains responsive and does not break at narrow sidebar widths.\n- Verify with all priority levels and agent types (Coder, Reviewer).",
